description:
This is a 7 minute workout called 'How to Start Calisthenics at Home For Beginners (No Equipment)' from the channel Pierre Dalati.
The workout falls under Strength/Calisthenics and Strength/Body weight.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
The workout has a The Foundation Builder and The Progression Quest vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner and Intermediate.
The effort required is Light and Moderate.

Calisthenics uses your body weight as resistance, making it a convenient and effective workout that can be done at home. To start, create a simple routine consisting of basic movements such as push-ups, squats, and sit-ups. Make sure to warm up properly with light cardio and stretching to prevent injury.
